47.42	European_sovereign_debt_crisis	European sovereign-debt crisis	The European sovereign debt crisis (commonly referred to by analysts as the ESDC) is an ongoing financial crisis that has made it difficult or impossible for some countries in the euro area to re-finance their government debt without the assistance of third parties.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Long-term_interest_rates_%28eurozone%29.png/300px-Long-term_interest_rates_%28eurozone%29.png
